of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John William Picton was born in 1365, in Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales, his father, William Picton, was 25 and his mother, Eleanor Millard, was 33. He had at least 1 daughter with Margaret verch Thomas Fort. He died in 1442, in Picton Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales, at the age of 77."},"et":{"1365–1442":"1365–1442","1372–1427":"1372–1427","1364–1427":"1364–1427","1387–1441":"1387–1441","1422–1460":"1422–1460","1340–1422":"1340–1422","1332–1423":"1332–1423","17 February 1387":"17. veebruar 1387","1340":"1340","1460":"1460","1372":"1372","30 April 1441":"30. aprill 1441","1423":"1423","1422":"1422","1365":"1365","1442":"1442","1332":"1332","1387":"1387","1441":"1441","1364":"1364","about 1364":"umbes 1364","30 November 1423":"30. november 1423","1427":"1427","Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales":"Newport, Monmouthshire, Wales","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Robeston West, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Robeston West, Pembrokeshire, Wales","Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Haverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, Wales","Picton Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Picton Castle, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1365–1442":"1365–1442","1372–1